            <span class="utterance" who="#gutmanE" start="440.846" end="x">... in the middle of the street, that is, just like dogs. And many Jews, forgetting that they were already disqualified as humans, would forget themselves and get on the sidewalk, such a thing happened also to myself, and then we would be beaten up, not by the Germans, but, alas, by the Lithuanians with whom we have lived together for hundreds of years, and thanks to whom [us] they have to come to learn what a pair of shoes are. Because before they were called the Lithuanian Klumpes, that means wooden shoes. More than that, they were [once] unable to achieve in their lives, and beyond this they enjoyed [once] no comfort.</span>
        </li>
