                        <a class="term" href="#vothG_commandant">commandant</a> [concentration camp <a class="term" href="#vothG_commandant">commandant</a>]. His name was Geke, Geke [Gerke?]. He was a top Obersturm-[?]-<a class="term" href="#vothG_fuehrer">Fuehrer</a>, that is, of the highest ranks of the German party. From the beginning he revealed himself as an intelligent person. He inquired about the state of nutrition on the <a class="term" href="#vothG_ghetto">ghetto</a> so Dr. Elkes reported [that it consists] of fifty grams of bread, so he said that of course on this the <a class="term" href="#vothG_ghetto">ghetto</a> couldn't live, the people must get more, they must get butter, and they must get other things. And they started giving butter but unfortunately it has cost... [there was a price for it]...</span>
